  <text xml:space="preserve">==cover== Statement of Work Agreement Between CLIENT and SUPPLIER Project Name: PROJECTNAME Project Number: AGREEMENTNUMBER ==agreement== Project Statement of Work for PROJECTNAME By signing below, each of us agrees to the terms on this page and the following pages. This Statement of Work (.SOW.) and any Modifications make up the entire agreement between both of us regarding the Services SUPPLIER(.Supplier.) provides to CLIENT in support of your project referred to as PROJECTNAME. These replace all previous agreements and other communications between both of us regarding these Services. This Statement of Work is valid until AGREEMENTDUEDATE. Agreed to: CLIENT CLIENTADDRESS Agreed to: SUPPLIER SUPPLIERADDRESS By: _________________________________________ By: _________________________________________ Name: _________________________________________ Name: _________________________________________ Title: _________________________________________ Title: Date: _________________________________________ Date: _________________________________________ ==Document Information== Document Source This document is maintained as an online document. Contact the author for the latest version. Revision History Version No. Date Summary of changes Revision Marks Ver 0.1 Draft Ver 0.2 Revised after Review Under this SOW, Supplier will provide Services to CLIENT. The Services Supplier provides are described in the section of this SOW entitled "Supplier.s Responsibilities". ==Project Description== 1. Project Description Discuss the background to the project . how was it initiated, etc. Cross-reference to CLIENT project artifacts. Identify, at a high level, the business needs / objectives that the project will address. If the project is part of a program or a larger initiative, describe the overall scope of program and where this project fits within the program. Describe the influences and dependencies between this project and any other on-going projects. This Statement of Work reflects the efforts to plan, initiate, execute, control and close the project as per the PMI PMBOK. For this project, the Supplier agrees to: 1. Gather, identify, analyze and manage the requirements 2. Document steps and activities required to fulfill the requirements. 3. Complete the following documents for approval of CLIENT: . Project Statement to initiate, build and implement the solution; . Requirements Specification / Macro Design Document; . Macro Design Certificate of Completion; . Test Plans; . Detailed Design Document; . Detailed Design Certificate of Completion; . Source Code (if software project); . Test Results Document; . Build & Supplier Testing Certificate of Completion; . User Acceptance Testing Certificate of Completion; . Implementation Plan; . Implementation Certificate of Completion; . Project Evaluation Report; and . Close Certificate of Completion. ==Supplier Responsibilities== 2. Supplier.s Responsibilities Supplier will perform the following Supplier Responsibilities : . Identify technical risks, dependencies, schedule requirements, resource constraints and business events that may affect the project; . Analyze business rules and current processing to produce a Requirements Specification document; . Define a solution; . Confirm that the architecture of the solution conforms to CLIENT Standards; . Prepare test plans; . Define the detailed design; . Build the solution and conduct the planned tests; . Prepare the implementation plan; . Coordinate testing and implementation of the project, and . Create the deliverables listed in section 3.0 Project Deliverables. ==Project Deliverables== 3. Project Deliverables Specify a bulleted list of the specific .deliverables. or .outputs. resulting from the project. Usually these are tangible things that we create or acquire which the client gets to keep (e.g. written documents) Also identify those .project management. deliverables that you will provide to the client. Usually these are PM related documents such as plans, reports, change and issue management documents, etc.) Each of the deliverables should indicate the completion of one or more scope items and consequently, either individually or cumulatively, should indicate the achievement of a project objective. ANSWER THE QUESTION . What tangible work product / output will be .delivered. to the customer to signify completion of a piece of work? The Deliverables to be produced by Supplier are: . Project Statement to initiate, build and implement the solution; . Requirements Specification / Macro Design Document; . Macro Design Certificate of Completion; . Test Plans for Unit and System/Integration Testing; . Detailed Design Document; . Detailed Design Certificate of Completion; . Source Code; . Test Results Document; . Build & Supplier Testing Certificate of Completion; . User Acceptance Testing Certificate of Completion; . Implementation Plan; . Implementation Certificate of Completion; . Project Evaluation Report; and . Close Certificate of Completion. . those deliverables as a result of the successful fulfillment of responsibilities as described in Section 2 above. ==Client Responsibilities== 4. CLIENT Responsibilities CLIENT will perform the CLIENT Responsibilities as described in CONTRACT . Identify business requirements and coordinate User input to requirements gathering and specification; . Identify constraints and solution guidelines that will apply to the solution; . Identify business risks, dependencies, schedule requirements, resource constraints and business events that may affect the project; . Define User Acceptance Test Plans and perform User Acceptance Testing; . Identify, specify and implement any needed changes to business processes; . Plan and deliver User documentation and training, if required; . Define business tests; . Prepare test environments and load test data for all testing; . Execute the Implementation work plan, and . Approve the deliverables. In addition, CLIENT agrees to: . Make available critical project Resources and Subject Matter Experts as identified in the mutually agreed Project Schedule; . Provide advice, guidance and assistance in working with CLIENT.s third party vendors; . Provide a CLIENT Project Manager, who will: . Have the authority to act on behalf of CLIENT in matters pertaining to the Project services; . Provide any decisions, approvals and information within three working days of receiving a request, unless stated otherwise in this Statement of Work; . Obtain authorizations for Supplier and our subcontractors to access, use and modify non-SUPPLIER products or information, necessary for Supplier to fulfill their obligations under this Statement of Work, without violating any third party.s rights. For greater certainty, Supplier is relieved of any obligations adversely affected by CLIENT.s failure to obtain the required authorizations; . Be the single point of contact for the management of the CLIENT obligations under the project; . Serve as the interface between the Supplier team members under this SOW and the CLIENT business functions, units and Affiliates; . Provide operational guidance to, manage and be accountable for the performance of the CLIENT personnel assigned to the project services; . Attend project planning, review and status meetings as required; . Coordinate and schedule the attendance of CLIENT Personnel as required to meet CLIENT.s responsibilities under this SOW; . Ensure that the Supplier PM is included in Project meetings and discussions. . Assist in the resolution of project issues or escalate as needed; . Establish and maintain the necessary controls for those areas of the Project Services for which the CLIENT has responsibility; . Provide review of and confirm that Deliverables meet the Completion Criteria set forth in the Statement of Work; . Communicate to CLIENT Internal Departments and to CLIENT Customers; . Initiate, coordinate and be accountable for the efforts of third party vendors where required. Add detailed description of our expectations of CLIENT for this SOW. ==Key Assumptions== 5. Key Assumptions This SOW and Supplier's estimates to perform this SOW are based on the following key assumptions, and those listed in the activities in Section 1 Project Description. Deviations that arise during the proposed Project will be managed through the Project change control process (.Project Change Request.) as described in Appendix A, and may result in adjustments to the scope of the Project including changes to: . The Project Duration, estimated milestone schedule, Budget, Service Levels, Resources utilized under this SOW, Operating Costs and impacts to the Services Environment if any. If an assumption deviation is not resolved through the Project Change Request within 10 Business Days then either party may exercise its rights in accordance with this Agreement. 1. Participation of and access to key CLIENT business representatives will be provided as described in the section CLIENT Responsibilities. 2. CLIENT will provide all necessary funding for non-labour expenses including travel, hardware, software and tools licenses, support and remote connectivity in accordance with the Agreement. 3. Supplier will provide the Services under this SOW during Business Hours. For the purposes of this Transition SOW, Business Hours are Monday to Friday 8 am to 4.30 pm Mountain Time except Statutory Holidays. If necessary, CLIENT agrees to provide after-hours access to CLIENT Facilities to Supplier Personnel. Supplier Personnel may work hours other than those defined as Business Hours to accommodate Project schedules. ==Estimates== 6. Estimated Schedule and Project Duration SUPPLIER will normally perform the Services during Business Hours (as previously defined) starting on STARTDATE and ending on ENDDATE (called the .End Date.). Some time may be required outside of normal business hours during project implementations. If CLIENT approval of this SOW is later than 10 days after submission of the SOW, the End Date may be modified. The following are the Project milestones: Milestone Description Estimated Completion Date Requirements Specification / Macro Design Document YYYYMMDD delivered to Client 2. Project Statement Document delivered to Client YYYYMMDD 3. Test Plans for Unit and System/Integration Testing YYYYMMDD delivered to Client 4. Detailed Design Document delivered to Client YYYYMMDD 5. Source Code ready for System Testing YYYYMMDD 6. Test Results Document delivered to Client YYYYMMDD 7. Implementation Plan delivered to Client YYYYMMDD 8. Project Evaluation Report delivered to Client YYYYMMDD 9. Close Certificate of Completion submitted to Client YYYYMMDD 7. Estimated Fees and Expenses Project fees will be calculated as described below. If any additional Supplier resources are required or if there are any material changes to cost estimates, it will be subject to CLIENT approval in accordance with Project Change Request process in Appendix A. Estimated Skill Classification Hours Hourly Rate Estimated Charges ___________________________________________________________________________ Project Manager RESOURCETYPE1 RESOURCETYPE2 Executive Oversight ___________________________________________________________________________ Estimated Total $ RESOURCEPRICE Travel Expenses ___________________________________________________________________________ Estimated Total $ TRAVELPRICE Per Diem and Lodging Expenses ___________________________________________________________________________ Estimated Total $ PERDIEMPRICE Communication Fee ___________________________________________________________________________ Estimated Total $ COMMUNICATIONPRICE Our total fees and expenses for this SOW are thus estimated to be: $ESTIMATEPRICE (.Estimated Total Price.) Supplier is providing Services under this SOW on a .time and materials. basis. Should additional work be requested in a Project Change Request, CLIENT agrees to pay our charges for the actual time expended (.Time Charges.). Invoices will be presented monthly based on Time Charges. ==Resources== 8. Resources Key Supplier Personnel . TBD Subcontractors . Supplier does not plan to use subcontractors for this SOW. ==Risk Analysis== 9. Risk Analysis List any risk factors associated with the project. The risks may lie in the target solution or the overall approach to achieve it. Identify planned responses for these risks and who will perform them. The following risks to the proposed Project are known to the Supplier and the measures being taken by the Supplier or requested of CLIENT to address those risks are described below PROJECT RISK PROBABILITY (H/M/L) IMPACT (H/M/L) MITIGATION PLAN The scope of the project may change beyond that described in this Statement of Work. L M Changes will be managed through the .Appendix A. project change control procedures. Availability of CLIENT Business resources to define requirements, plan the User Acceptance Test and perform User Acceptance Testing. L H Escalate to CLIENT PM, to ensure the resources are available during the project duration. Changes will be managed through the .Appendix A. project change control procedures. Resources may not be available during the desired timeframe. M H Assess schedule impacts and if necessary, manage change through the .Appendix A. project change control procedures. ==Operating Costs== 10. Operating Costs Estimated changes in the cost of the Services Environment, Support Services and any other infrastructure or technology costs that will be incurred in the operation of the changed Application are described below: . No effect on operating costs for the Services Environment and Support Services is anticipated ==Completion Criteria== 11. Completion Criteria Supplier will have fulfilled its obligations under this SOW when any one of the following first occurs: . Supplier accomplishes the Supplier activities described in this Statement of Work and a Notice of Acceptance has been issued by CLIENT; or . This Statement of Work is suspended, cancelled or terminated in accordance with Appendix B. ==Administrative Information== 12. Administrative Information CLIENT Project Sponsor: _______________________________ CLIENT Project Manager: _______________________________ SUPPLIER Delivery Manager: To be named. SUPPLIER Project Manager: To be named. ==Appendix A== Appendix A: Project Procedures A - 1: Project Change Control Procedure The following process will be followed if a change to this SOW is required. . A Project Change Request (PCR) will be the vehicle for communicating change. The PCR must describe the change, the rationale for the change and the effect the change will have on the Project. . The designated project manager of the requesting party will review the proposed change and determine whether to submit the request to the other party. . Both of the CLIENT Project Manager and the SUPPLIER Project Manager will review the proposed change and recommend it for further investigation or reject it. Supplier will specify any charges for such investigation. A PCR must be signed by authorized representatives from both parties to authorize investigation of the recommended changes. Supplier will invoice CLIENT for any charges associated with such investigation. The investigation will determine the effect that the implementation of the PCR will have on price, schedule, deliverables and other components as set out in this SOW including any impact on scope, terms or conditions of the Agreement. . A Change Order or Project Change Request must be signed by authorized representatives from both of CLIENT and SUPPLIER to authorize implementation of the investigated changes. Until a change is agreed in writing, both parties will continue to act in accordance with the latest agreed version of the SOW. ==Appendix B== SOW suspension or termination This statement may be suspended at any time under the following conditions: CLIENT provides written Notice of Suspension, and a Project Change Request; CLIENT agrees to pay: all costs incurred to date; all costs for Travel required to return resources to their home locations; all per diem charges required to return resources to their home location; CLIENT provides an expected project resumption date; This statement of work may be terminated at the checkpoint of each phase without penalty. To terminate this SOW, CLIENT agrees to: Provide written Notice of Termination; Provide a Project Change Request; Complete a Project Closure; If this SOW is terminated before Project Completion, the CLIENT agrees to pay: all costs for Time and Materiels incurred to date; all costs for Travel incurred to date, or required to return resources to their home locations; all per diem charges incurred to date, or will be incurred returning resources to their home location; all costs for Time and Materiels to close the project; * * * END * * * [[Category:IBM]][[Category:Contract]]</text> 
