applicable option. The contract or proposal will include only standard IBM T&C's or slight deviations approved by C&N. The contract will include some slight deviations from standard IBM T&C's that have not been approved by IBM legal or C&N. The contract requires terms which significantly deviate from standard IBM T&C's and have been approved by Legal and/or C&N (e.g., liability change). The contract requires terms which significantly deviate from standard IBM T&C's and have NOT been X approved by legal and C&N. b. Work Arrangements Refers to contractual payment obligations Check the MOST applicable option. Hourly services or time and materials with no committed deliverables. Fixed price standard offerings and the effort is well-bounded. Hourly services or time and materials with committed deliverables. Fixed price with the ability to re-price by phase. The planned work arrangements are T&M with a price cap Multi-phase, fixed price bid with no ability to reprice during the contract. X ===Part II=== a. Client Responsibilities Check the MOST applicable option. The client is expected to have all prerequisites (for example, business process reengineering or training) complete in time for IBM to meet its responsibilities. There is some concern as to whether the client has the skills, time or capability to meet its responsibilities for a successful project There is significant concern as to whether the client has the skills, time or capability to meet its X responsibilities for the project b. Scope Baseline Check the MOST applicable option. The scope baseline document is clear and unambiguous The scope baseline document is broad, vauge, not completely bound or based solely on IBM's interpretation X of the requirements c. Accessibility Check the MOST applicable option. There are no accessibility requirements in this proposed solution. Accessibility requirements are included in this proposed solution. IBM product assessments have been requested through the IBM Accessibility Center. Accessibility requirements are included in this proposed solution. IBM product assessments have not been requested. Risk Statements Applicable to this project Prop RM HQQA Accessibility requirements for the proposed solution have not yet been determined. X ==F. Risks== 1. Technical and Delivery Assessment (TDA) Review Refers to the TDA review conducted on the solution by an SME or team independent of the proposal team. The review should include a technical risk assessment using GS Risk technical path Check the MOST applicable option. A TDA for this kind of services / contract is not necessary and has not been performed or a TDA was performed by a qualified expert and all concerns have been addressed.. The TDA was conducted but some concerns were not yet closed. A TDA is necessary but has not been performed. X 2. Safety and Security Check the MOST applicable option. There are no safety or security risks involved with this proposed solution. The proposed solution or service relates to: 1) physical security assessment; 2) physical access control; 3) identity authentication or clearance (such as with biometrics, smart cards, or the provision of sensitive information on individuals); 4) physical surveillance; 5) weapons; 6) nuclear, biological, chemical, or other hazardous materials; 7) aviation, railway, seaport, or cargo security; 8) money laundering; 9) physical threat detection, analysis or response; 10) performing application development or systems integration for a client of an application or system that collects, assembles, or evaluates personally identifiable information concerning creditworthiness, criminal background, immigration status or suspicion of unlawful activity; 11) the creation of a universal personal identification card system; 12) risk-scoring (criminal, border control, financial or otherwise). The proposed solution relates to advising clients about business processes or information technology in the X context of compliance with any law (e.g., a law relating to privacy or security, such as HIPAA, Gramm-Leach-Bliley, SOX Compliance, FDA rules, or the European Union Directive). (Note that IBM consultants are prohibited from providing legal services or advice.) 3. Subject Matter Advisors This section refers to advisors such as pricing, C&N, Business Managers, Global Facilitation Centre advisors, etc. This section is not intended to cover technical Subject Matter Experts. Check the MOST applicable option. All required subject matter advisors have been consulted as part of the bid process. All required subject matter advisors have not yet been consulted as part of the bid process. X 4. Risk Management Plans Check the MOST applicable option. A risk management plan has been defined (even if preliminary at proposal stage) and will be executed during the project. No risk management plan (even preliminary) has been planned X ==G. Supplier Benefits== 1. Financial Risks Check the MOST applicable option. Neither investment nor risk sharing is part of this opportunity. The opportunity will include risk sharing, investment, penalties or other financial risks X 2. Cost Case Check the MOST applicable option. Risk Statements Applicable to this project Prop RM HQQA The cost case matches the staff plan and there is confidence in the cost case (for instance Risk Management, pricer, or financial analyst and SME during TDA has reviewed the cost case and agrees). Rate increases and promotion estimates over the life of the project have not been incorporated when calculating the fees. The cost of financing non-standard payment terms has not been fully factored into the cost case for the project. There are concerns with the cost case (for instance it does not match the staff plan or the cost case was not reviewed completely by an SME during the TDA review). There are significant concerns with the cost case (for instance it does not match the staff plan or no review X has been conducted). 3. Payment Terms Check the MOST applicable option. Payment to be billed as work is completed or by identified dates. Payment schedule based on deliverables or milestones that are spaced less than 30 days apart. Payment schedule based on deliverables or milestones that are spaced more than 30 days apart. Terms implying that IBM may carry contract costs for extended periods and Time Value of Money provisions are not included in the pricing case. Payments based on benefits received (Risk Sharing/Transaction pricing without guaranteed standard profit). X 4. Requirements for Performance, Availability or Service Levels Check the MOST applicable option. Standard or no requirements. Requirements for performance, a vailability or service levels with penalies X 5. Delivery Commencement Outside of Normal Contracts Check the MOST applicable option. Not Applicable Work will begin under a "Letter of Authorization" or similar contract only. Project activities may commence before the contract is executed. In addition to a draft contract, there are other written or verbal commitments with respect to this project (for X example, clarification letters). ==H. Proposal/ SOW Completeness== 1. Proposal / SOW Check the MOST applicable option. The Proposal/SOW is completely documented The Proposal work scope is broad, vague, or not completely bounded but there will be an opportunity for it to be clarified in a final SOW prior to contract execution The Proposal does not contain all required elements of an SOW or if at contract execution phase the SOW is X not completely documented. 2. Proposal/SOW Documentation Readiness Refers to the basic elements required for a complete SOW or proposal. Even if a formal SOW will not be submitted, the following elements should be included in the proposal a. IBM Team Roles and Responsibilities Check the MOST applicable option. The roles and responsibilities for IBM staff have been clearly defined in the proposal, Statement of Work and estimates. Risk Statements Applicable to this project Prop RM H