h consistent use of methodologies and timely and effective project execution ensuring high quality client deliverables meeting schedule requirements within budget. (2.3) Grow the business by helping to qualify and close strategic sector and industry-based opportunities. Lead proposal teams and secure client approval. Proactively sell up in customer engagements. Build sustainable client relationships at targeted accounts. (3) Delivered Globally (and Locally): (3.1) Contribute positively to the financial and utilization targets of 83.7/92.7% our AS Calgary Practice. My personal target will be xx%. (3.2) Ensure compliance with IBM Business controls and processes: AS Policy, IGSDF, Full-labour Claiming, Expenses, PD Tool Skill Assessments, updated Resume, WST and PBC/IDP. (3.3) Achieve and maintain effective Business Controls; drive across delivery teams, collate, review and address business controls improvements. Achieve satisfactory quarterly controls; Key Control Over operations (KCO), Corporate Audits, Business Controls proactive reviews, Data Security and Privacy practices and ensure NO Qualified SAS70 or AUP reports. (3.4) Demonstrate understanding and compliance with Delivery Excellence; AMS Best Practices, Customer Satisfaction-ICES, ICHC, COScards, Financial Management, Project & Portfolio Management, and Risk Management. https://w3.webahead.ibm.com/w3ki/display/DECANADA/Home (3.5) Achieve consistent usage of Globally Integrated End-to-End process, methods, metrics and tools to drive DE. Maintain compliance to the appropriate industry standards . CMMI, ITIL, SOX. Demonstrate adherence to GBS and AS Policies, increased PM Competency focus, ensure Method Adoption workshops are conducted, improve on C/D projects, and reduce year-to-year profit leakage. (3.6) Participate in hiring and recruiting efforts by helping define capacity and skill needs, identifying and interviewing candidates, and recommending hiring decisions. (3.7) Adopt IBM GBS standard processes, practices and tools in support of consistency in delivery, productivity and efficiency and superior capability. (3.8) Refer to Senior Project Manager - Band 9 for additional goals where your role includes managing engagements. 4. Additional AS Calgary & role specific goals: - Attend and provide feedback to quarterly department meetings. Attendance via phone or in person is expected. - Participate/lead in giveback activities: Spirit Events, Calgary IBM Club, Mentoring, Lunch n Learns, Other Community Events (e.g. Junior Achievement) - Provide timely and constructive feedback both informally and on Feedback forms (EOE, Project Assessment) - Expenses to be submitted within 60 days of expense occurring. ILC to be submitted by Friday Noon. - (Band 7, 8 & 9) Involved in presentation at Blue Horizon 2008 or RTLE People Management Goals: If you have people management responsibilities what are your 2-4 goals for how you will lead people effectively and create a climate where employees excel? Refer to The 7 People Management Indicators if you have people management responsibilities. Development Goals: What are your1-2 development goals that will enhance your ability to meet your business goals for this assessment period? Your development goals should be supported by your IDP and other development processes available. Develop and execute a skills development plan that is aligned with the Organizational Training Roadmap. http://w3-03.ibm.com/services/gbs/americas/gbs_me/canada/en/lk/otr/index.html Contribute to and support an inclusive environment by understanding, communicating and demonstrating that diversity drives innovation and growth at IBM. Complete and maintain my certification/Professional Development Framework (PDF) Level 5 as required by your profession and assist others to do the same. Coach or assist in identifying and developing other professionals for future technical leadership roles with focus on strengthening the diversity representation. Mentor at least one other professional to develop future leaders with focus on strengthening the diversity representation. Contribute .give back. to GBS (such as Intellectual Capital, Sharenets, Lunch and Learns). The 7 People Management Indicators Do you hold profiles, i.e., according to BluePages? If yes, what are your goals for how you will lead people effectively and create a climate where employees excel? If no, but you have People Management responsibilities, e.g., Project Manager, review the people management goals and add 2-4 to your Business Goals section. These are seven indicators for excellence in People Management. They should help you lead high performance through people. 1. Ensure employees understand how their work contributes to IBM's strategy, market success and your organization's goals. 2. Lead by example, set clear performance standards, provide straightforward feedback in a respectful way, and actively manage low contributors. 3. Recognize outstanding contributions by employees and teams. 4. Ensure a positive performance climate; listen to employees, address their issues and help employees succeed in IBM's matrix environment. 5. Foster teamwork and inclusion among all employees -- across locations, cultures and geos -- and promote IBM's value of diversity. 6. Encourage employees to be innovative, and support ideas that should be implemented. 7. Develop the people with whom you work, teach what you know, and continually set clear development plans and goals for every employee reporting to you. Foundational Competencies for ALL Practitioners Passion for the Business: Display a level of enthusiasm for and pride in IBM and in one.s own job/work that inspires others. Drive to Achieve: Accomplish challenging goals and look for ways to improve outcomes; consistently overcome obstacles to produce high quality results; actively seek to acquire new knowledge and improve skills. Client Insight: Understand internal and external clients. business, needs and goals from the client.s point of view; build rapport with clients, anticipate clients. needs and respond appropriately to their concerns and problems. Taking Ownership: Proactively identify and take responsibility for tasks and decisions in a timely manner. Adaptability: Demonstrate flexibility in dealing with situations involving changing demands, uncertainty, and stress; modify goals and direction as needed; maintain focus despite conflicting demands. Creative Problem Solving: Apply logical methods to solve problems; conduct thorough fact-finding and appropriate analysis; anticipate potential problems and plan accordingly; efficiently consider alternative, creative solutions and identify the most appropriate solution. Trustworthiness: Demonstrate integrity and professionalism in dealing with clients and IBMers. Teamwork: Collaborate and work effectively with individuals and teams inside and outside IBM, respect and value others. differences, build and strengthen relationships; achieve win-win solutions. Communication: Speak and write in a clear, concise and organized way; communicate openly and honestly; listen carefully to others to ensure understanding; match mode and style of communication to situation and audience; understand and effectively utilize available communication tools. Leadership Competencies for Intermediate/Senior Roles Client Partnering: Outstanding IBM Leaders establish strong and long lasting partnerships with their clients (internal and external) based on trust, credibility, and relevance, and are energized by their clients' success. Collaborative Influence: Outstanding IBM leaders actively create and promote cross-boundary collaboration to do the right thing for IBM and its' clients-regardless of formal authority. These leaders facilitate collaboration to address short- and longer-term efforts by getting the right people together from across IBM, articulating and enforcing norms of how the team will work together, and securing organizational support to enable a collaborative agenda. Embracing Challenge: Outstanding IBM leaders see opportunity in complex and challenging situations. They get energized by complex and challenging problems and take personal responsibility to ensure that they are resolved. These leaders are able to do this by identifying the central issue in the complexity and getting themselves and others focused on addressing those "vital few" priorities. They take accountability enthusiastically while accurately conveying the risk or difficulty involved. These leaders' enthusiasm and their belief in a positive outcome in difficult situations inspire others to believe they can succeed and embrace the challenge themselves. Think Horizontally: Outstanding IBM leaders think creatively, considering issues from multiple divergent perspectives. They think across boundaries, beginning from the end-user or client's customer while making connections across the various parts of IBM, partners, and suppliers. They synthesize these perspectives from within and outside IBM, leveraging the IBM enterprise to create innovative solutions and increase opportunities to grow ahead of the market. Informed Judgment: Outstanding IBM leaders possess a level of objectivity in making timely decisions. Their decisions are based on data, facts, and perspectives gathered from a broad range of sources. They test their first impressions with other people, and use facts and data to inform and shape their decisions and subsequent actions. They integrate the facts with their intuition and their acquired expertise. This enables them to make decisions with confidence and an appropriate sense of urgency. Strategic Risk Taking: Outstanding IBM leaders seize opportunities for innovation and business growth. They focus on identifying and driving forward bold, relevant and strategic opportunities from concept to reality. They do this in the face of significant risk and despite resistance, using their own determination and resilience, collaborating to leverage resources within and outside IBM. They balance cost and benefits over the short and long term, taking appropriate risk to drive profitable and sustainable growth in pursuit of IBM's vision. Earning Trust: Outstanding IBM leaders respect the uniqueness of every person. They develop trusting relationships with all the people with whom they work, both inside and outside of IBM. They follow through on commitments and act with integrity. They refrain from cynicism and blaming when problems occur. Instead, they appreciate the unique strengths, limitations, and potential of people and develop mutually beneficial relationships based on positive regard for the individual and their organization, whether inside or outside of IBM. They do what is right for the long-term good of the relationship even at the risk of a short-term or personal cost. Enabling Performance and Growth: Outstanding IBM leaders focus on strategic priorities to provide on-going clarity to their own and extended teams. They anticipate and remove obstacles that interfere with the ability of these teams to achieve objectives and pursue business growth. They demonstrate the courage to challenge influential people in order to remove inhibitors to performance. This includes supporting others as they take significant entrepreneurial risk and protecting them from inappropriate consequences. These leaders challenge prevailing practices to make lasting and systemic changes that improve the performance of our people and grow the business. Developing IBM People and Communities: Outstanding IBM leaders proactively commit their time and effort to develop themselves and other individuals, teams, and communities in IBM. They set an example through their own personal growth and development, as well as by coaching and mentoring others. These leaders create, support, and participate in communities for developing capability in others and promoting a sense of association. They also proactively take accountability for developing the future leaders of IBM both inside and outside their own organizations. Passion for IBM.s Future: Outstanding IBM leaders are passionate about IBM's capabilities and opportunities for making a positive difference in the world. This passion comes from realizing that IBM's values and heritage are consistent with their personal values, convictions, and aspirations as leaders. These outstanding leaders not only want to win in the marketplace, but also deeply believe in the quality and breadth of IBM's exceptional capability. Their enthusiasm and passion energizes others to achieve IBM's unique potential to transform business and society. [[Category:IBM]][[Category:Contract]]</text> 
