  <text xml:space="preserve">==Core Capabilities== Core capabilities are the business and interpersonal skills that underpin our success in the industry. They reflect the behaviors that enable each of us to: ===Build and maintain relationships with clients and colleagues=== Deliver results in line with the expectations of our clients, company, and colleagues Demonstration of Core Capabilities The core capabilities of Business, Leadership and Relationship are reflected to some degree in every employee, at every level, in our global team. They define who we are and how we do business. They capture the richness of the wide range of roles across the business. Core capabilities can be demonstrated in different ways, depending on your role. For example, a stand-alone .process guru. requires an element of Leadership, but may demonstrate it in terms of ideas, concepts, and methods - as opposed to demonstrating leadership through large-scale people management. ===PD Framework: Core Capabilities=== The three core capabilities that apply across IBM are reflected in the PD Framework: Business, Leadership and Relationship. Each core capability is further defined by a number of sub-elements (see table below). Each sub-element contains a set of behaviors that IBM professionals are expected to demonstrate. While all of the individual behaviors within the sub-elements are significant, GBS has identified a set of these behaviors that is of particular importance to GBS. These are the behaviors against which you will be evaluated, and which you will be expected to demonstrate, in order to achieve the next level in core capabilities. To view behaviors for each core capability level, click on the sub-elements in the table below. ====Business==== *Risk Management *Pricing Concepts* *Proposal Development *Financial Analysis *IBM Infrastructure *Strategic Business Themes * Pricing Concepts is required only if the practitioner.s role requires that set of behaviors. ====Leadership==== *Knowledge Management *Performance Management *Professional Vitality *Team Building *Project Management ====Relationship==== *Engagement Management *Communication *Negotiation *Managing Organization Change *Winning Business ===Assessment Guidance=== For guidance that will help you apply the core capabilities to your work on projects AND provide assessment guidelines for whole level move PDF applications, see the "Core Capabilities Assessment Guidance" document in the References, Downloads, and Training section of this website. This document contains the following information: *Overview of the core capabilities *Description of the how the behavioral capabilities relate to the core capabilities *Definition of the proficiency levels *Examples of how the core capabilities might be demonstrated on projects *Guidelines for whole level moves in Business, Leadership, and Relationship Core Capabilities are assessed in Career Point. The Career Point Quick Reference Guide, found on the Career Point web page, provides instructions for adding the Career Point database to your workstation. ===PD Framework Core Capabilities: Business=== ====Risk Management==== Foundation: - Understand, articulate and provide recommendations to minimize risks associated with assigned projects or tasks Experienced: - Understand, articulate and develop risk mitigation recommendations that contribute to the successful execution of projects, typically of medium or large size and/or complexity. Advanced: - Anticipate, articulate and mitigate risks for successful design and execution of large, multiple and/or complex projects. ===Pricing Concepts Required only if your role requires this set of behaviors.=== Foundation: - Understand basic pricing concepts for services/solutions (e.g., basic transaction pricing, value pricing, profitability dynamics). Understand the fundamental concepts of the Quality Assurance (QA) process and how pricing is affected. Experienced: - Apply pricing concepts for services/solutions (e.g., transaction pricing, value pricing, profitability models) to assigned projects. Understand and support the Quality Assurance (QA) process for pricing approval. Advanced: - Articulate and manage transaction pricing, value pricing and profitability models. Understand the applicability of creative pricing models and techniques when structuring proposals. Execute and leverage the Quality Assurance (QA) process for pricing approval. ====Proposal Development==== Foundation: - Understand and articulate elements of solutions/proposals to include clearly identified objectives, scope, benefits, costs, responsibilities, assumptions, deliverables, schedules, completion criteria and resource requirements needed to execute engagements successfully. Understand and support the Quality Assurance (QA) process.. Experienced: - Define and prepare solutions/proposals that clearly identify objectives, scope, benefits, costs, responsibilities, assumptions, deliverables, schedules, completion criteria and resource requirements needed to execute small- to medium-sized engagements successfully. Articulate and support the Quality Assurance (QA) process. Advanced: - Lead the definition and preparation of solutions/proposals and plans that clearly identify objectives, scope, benefits, costs, responsibilities, assumptions, deliverables, schedules, completion criteria and resource requirements needed to execute large and/or complex engagements successfully. - Execute and leverage the Quality Assurance (QA) process. ====Financial Analysis==== Foundation: - Understand basic financial management concepts and terms. Understand relationship of personal and project-level financial dynamics (e.g., project profitability, utilization, realization). Experienced: - Be able to apply general business and financial management concepts, principles and tools used by business unit to assist business decision-making and problem-solving (e.g., return on investment (ROI), expense control, profitability, depreciation, capital. Advanced: - Use, and mentor others in the use of, financial management concepts, principles and tools to perform business decision-making and problem-solving for both IBM and clients, as they apply to your business unit. ====IBM Infrastructure==== Foundation: - Learn and apply the fundamental IBM tools and processes to perform job-related responsibilities effectively (e.g., Lotus Notes, e-client workbench, productivity/mobility centers, Knowledge Portal). Understand the IBM organization and process for addressing business opportunities. Experienced: - Apply and lead the use of the fundamental IBM tools and processes to perform job-related responsibilities on projects of medium size and complexity effectively (e.g., Lotus Notes, e-client workbench, productivity/mobility centers, Knowledge Portal). Leverage the IBM organization and processes for developing business opportunities. Advanced: - Use, and mentor others in the use of, fundamental IBM tools and processes to perform job-related responsibilities on major business engagements effectively (e.g., Lotus Notes, e-client workbench, productivity/mobility centers, Knowledge Portal). Provide leadership in engaging the IBM organization collaboratively on business opportunities. ====Strategic Business Themes==== Foundation: - Understand the IBM value proposition, organization, business partners and process for addressing opportunities related to strategic focus areas. Experienced: - Leverage the IBM value proposition, organization, business partners, competitive position in the marketplace and process for addressing opportunities related to strategic focus areas. Advanced: - Provide leadership in engaging the IBM organization and appropriate business partners, in enhancing IBM.s competitive position in the marketplace, and in driving the process on identified opportunities related to strategic focus areas. ===PD Framework Core Capabilities: Leadership=== ====Knowledge Management==== Foundation: - Understand the process for finding and reusing existing intellectual capital (knowledge, experience, assets, etc.). Contribute to the sharing of business-relevant knowledge within and across the IBM team. Experienced: - Develop, and assist with management and development of, reusable intellectual capital and assets. Facilitate the sharing of business-relevant knowledge within and across the IBM team by participating in, and contributing to, one or more competency networks. Advanced: - Develop business-directing reusable intellectual capital and assets. Promote and facilitate the sharing of business-relevant knowledge within and across the IBM team by participating in, and contributing to, a competency network core team. ====Performance Management==== Foundation: - Maintain a positive attitude and demonstrate maturity in dealing with challenging situations. Provide constructive feedback on individual or group performance as requested. Motivate team members - IBM, client and subcontractor - using powers of persuasion, leadership, and formal delegation and follow-up techniques. Experienced: - Demonstrate leadership in using powers of persuasion, formal delegation and follow-up techniques. Manage time and work priorities for self and teams, to meet or exceed objectives and deadlines. Provide guidance, leadership and constructive feedback to team members. Advanced: - Lead and motivate team members, staff and executives to action, using powers of persuasion and formal delegation and follow-up techniques. Set direction, communicate and model effective leadership behaviors in dealing with individuals and teams and in managing business processes. Perform effectively as a leader and/or mentor for individuals in ways that will contribute to their personal growth and increased value to IBM. ====Professional Vitality==== Foundation: - Commit to personal growth and continuous learning, including consideration of advice and counsel of others. Share knowledge through limited skills mentoring. Experienced: - Perform effectively as a mentor for individuals in ways that enhance their personal growth and value to IBM. Manage individual flexibility and adaptability to optimize performance and continuous learning in a rapidly changing environment. Advanced: - Perform effectively as a mentor for individuals in ways that result in the development of future IBM leaders. Anticipate needs, manage and advise on individual flexibility and adaptability to optimize performance, on-the-job training opportunities, and continuous learning in a rapidly changing environment. ====Team Building==== Foundation: - Work together with IBM, client and subcontractor staff for common business purpose and for mutual success. Share ideas, lessons learned, and experience with others. Recognize and respect individual differences and diversity. Experienced: - Foster a sense of teaming among project members-- IBM, client and subcontractor-- and improve effectiveness of the overall team. Encourage and enable the sharing of ideas, lessons learned, and experience with others. Promote an environment of recognition and respect for individual differences and diversity. Advanced: - Set direction, communicate and model effective leadership behaviors. Create an environment and process for the sharing of ideas, lessons learned, and experience with others. Champion recognition and respect for individual differences and diversity. ====Project Management==== Foundation: - Understand fundamentals of project management in a customer or client environment. Learn project management tools and techniques as defined by project leader/engagement manager and/or practice. Experienced: - Apply fundamentals of project management when working on projects in a customer or client environment. Use project management tools and techniques as defined by project leader/engagement manager and/or practice. Advanced: - Demonstrate leadership in applying fundamentals of project management when working on projects in a customer or client environment. Use, and mentor the use of, project management tools and techniques as defined by project and/or practice requirements. ===PD Framework Core Capabilities: Relationship=== ====Engagement Management==== Foundation: - Support the resolution of project and business issues to the satisfaction of clients and IBM, and consistent with the Quality Assurance (QA) process. Understand the client internal culture and business environment. Support the effective management of personal utilization. Experienced: - Contribute to resolution of project and business issues, in a manner and with an outcome acceptable to the client and IBM, and consistent with Quality Assurance (QA) defined risk and financial measures. Understand client organizational hierarchy for assigned projects and apply knowledge to facilitate decision-making processes. Manage client expectations on assigned projects to ensure a high level of satisfaction. Advanced: - Resolve complex relationship and business issues, in a manner and with an outcome acceptable to the client and to IBM. Develop and foster strong trust-based relationships with customer/client senior-level management, yielding significant business results. Manage client expectations and act to achieve high client satisfaction. ====Communication==== Foundation: - Understand how to be an effective receiver of information-- through attention, analysis, validation and provision of feedback. Understand the critical communication considerations in meetings with IBM and customers/clients. Experienced: - Apply communication principles to build and support effective relationships, typically focusing on middle management and higher levels for assigned customers/clients and projects. Apply critical communication considerations in meetings with IBM and customers/clients. Advanced: - Apply communication principles to build and support effective relationships, typically focusing on senior management and executive levels for assigned customers/clients and projects. Effectively communicate vision, mission and goal concepts to IBM and client. Lead and mentor the application of critical communication considerations in meetings with IBM and customers/clients. ====Negotiation==== Foundation: - Understand and effectively evaluate alternate points of view and tradeoffs. Resolve issues within assigned project segments and personal domain. Experienced: - Understand, articulate and make effective decisions/recommendations regarding issues, alternate viewpoints and tradeoffs. Resolve issues within assigned/managed project segments and personal domain. Apply escalation process to issues requiring higher authority for resolution. Advanced: - Structure, facilitate and manage effective project-level and/or relationship-level issue resolution mechanisms. Understand, articulate and make effective decisions/recommendations regarding project-level and relationship-level issues, alternate viewpoints and tradeoffs. ====Managing Organization Change==== Foundation: - Understand the significance of organization change management in implementing new systems, processes and solutions. Support the implementation of organization change management actions and programs. Experienced: - Understand change management actions and programs sufficiently to make appropriate recommendations to accomplish desired organizational changes. Advanced: - Facilitate client awareness that organization change management actions and programs may be required to deal with the variety of organizational issues involved in implementing new systems, processes and solutions. ====Winning Business==== Foundation: - Recognize and articulate potential new business opportunities related to customer or client relationships. Learn IBM.s capabilities and offerings. Demonstrate commitment to customer/client satisfaction in executing daily tasks. Experienced: - Develop a tactical and strategic understanding of the customer or client business environment and needs. Proactively meet with customer or client professionals, management and executives to understand their concerns and goals. Understand IBM.s capabilities, offerings and business partner relationships, and be able to articulate them in customer or client terms. Acquire general knowledge of IBM.s primary service competitors and understand how to apply this knowledge to IBM.s advantage in the selling process. Advanced: - Develop and maintain a fundamental knowledge of the customer.s or client.s total business environment, including business issues, strategies, vision, goals, objectives, tactics and how they relate to IBM.s business objectives. Anticipate and proactively meet with customer or client professionals, management and executives on an as-needed basis to understand their concerns and goals. Understand IBM.s capabilities and offerings, and be able to articulate them in terms of executive-level concepts/benefits. Apply knowledge of IBM.s primary service competitors and business partner relationships to IBM.s advantage in the selling process. [[Category:IBM]][[Category:Contract]]</text> 
