  <comment>New page: ==Level 1== N/A ==Level 2== The capabilities below are performed with Moderate Supervision. 2.1 Used an approved PM methodology to manage projects or sub-projects that meet the foll...</comment> 
  <text xml:space="preserve">==Level 1== N/A ==Level 2== The capabilities below are performed with Moderate Supervision. 2.1 Used an approved PM methodology to manage projects or sub-projects that meet the following requirements: Number of projects: 2 Projects with IBM: 1 Projects completed in the last three years: - Duration of each project: minimum 3 months Projects with 2 or more FTEs: 2 Stages of the project lifecycle: 1 2.2 Accurately managed hours and expenses to budget 2.3 Formally reported status to project leadership to review progress against team and project objectives 2.4 Contributed to the definition of project requirements 2.5 Participated in informal project risk management activities 2.6 Raised issues and questions in a timely manner 2.7 Assigned project responsibilities, ensured successful completion of individual project tasks and contributed to the Project Assessments of team members 2.8 Developed and sustained business relationships with client during project execution ==Level 3== The capabilities below are performed with Limited Supervision. 3.1 Used an approved PM methodology to manage projects or sub-projects that meet the following requirements: Number of projects: 2 Projects with IBM: 1 Projects completed in the last three years: 1 Duration of each project: minimum 3 months Projects with 2 or more FTEs: 1 Projects with 5 or more FTEs: 1 Stages of the project lifecycle: 2 3.2 Managed project costs, assisted with financial management responsibilities, and contributed to the delivery of a project on time and on budget 3.3 Participated in project communications management (e.g. contributed to formal and consistent monthly status reports, such as Seven Keys) 3.4 Contributed to the development of the integrated project plan for entire project and developed the plan for team or subproject 3.5 Demonstrated knowledge of risk management practices by participating in formal project risk management activities 3.6 Understood scope boundaries and identified change requests that need to be elevated to project management 3.7 Raised issues and questions in a timely manner and recommended alternative solutions to resolve 3.8 Assigned project responsibilities, ensured successful completion of individual project tasks and completed Project Assessments 3.9 Managed client's expectations to avoid misunderstandings and to ensure client satisfaction 3.10 Defined types of intellectual capital to be used to add value to the project ==Level 4== The capabilities below are performed with Minimal Supervision. 4.1 Used an approved PM methodology to manage projects or sub-projects that meet the following requirements: Number of projects: 2 Projects with IBM: 1 Projects completed in the last three years: 1 Duration of each project: minimum 6 months Projects with 5 or more FTEs: 2 Stages of the project lifecycle: 2 Subcontractors: at least 1 The total value of all projects managed total either US$3M revenue or 22,000 total hours managed during time on project(s) 4.2 Contributed to the development of a SOW as part of a proposal effort 4.3 Developed staffing budgets and used IBM's financial systems and methods to manage project costs and deliver the project or sub-project as per the estimated cost and plan 4.4 Completed formal and consistent monthly status reports (e.g., Seven Keys) to provide assessment of project health and status and included issues for escalation as appropriate 4.5 Estimated, planned, developed, tracked, forecasted, and managed a component of an integrated project plan and used a consistent change management program to monitor and revise plan as appropriate 4.6 Developed and/or managed project risk management plans and responded to quality reviews as appropriate 4.7 Articulated the project baseline and scope, ensured that all team members (IBM, client and subcontractors) understood their impact on it, and implemented scope and change management processes to prevent occurrence of scope creep 4.8 Managed projects that meet at least one of the following criteria for 6 months: 1 - Early use of product/technology within country 2- Direct interface with multiple client stakeholders 4.9 Reviewed conditions of satisfaction with client or project success criteria with stakeholder on an ongoing basis to ensure GBS consistently met these conditions/ criteria and that the client was fulfilling their responsibilities 4.10 Resolved issues raised through formal issue management processes 4.11 Developed a Quality Plan and managed project quality 4.12 Monitored, tracked, controlled, validated, and reported status and quality of deliverables from project team members, including subcontractors, and completed Project Assessments in a timely manner 4.13 Developed, maintained, and managed relationships throughout the sponsor and project or program organizations to ensure client sponsorship, involvement, and commitment 4.14 Used internal IBM knowledge and external intellectual capital to enhance management of project ==Level 5== The capabilities below are performed Independently. Level 5 in this dimension is obtained either by moderation from EDM 4, if the professional is already IBM certified or waived at the Senior PM Level, or by initial PM certification at the Senior PM or Executive PM level, which now includes additional EDM5 criteria. Please go to the PM/COE certification page for further details. 5.1 Used an approved PM methodology to manage projects that meet the following requirements: Number of projects: 3 Projects with IBM: 1 Projects completed in the last three years: 1 Duration of each project: minimum 6 months - Projects with 5 or more FTEs: 2 - Projects with 10 or more FTEs: 1 Stages of the project lifecycle: all Subcontractors: multiple The total value of all projects managed total either US$7.5M revenue or 50,000 total hours managed during time on project(s) 5.2 Defined and documented a SOW that was used to define the agreement between IBM and the client and included the following elements: * Description of scope of work * Description of services * List of deliverables and the associated delivery and acceptance conditions * High level schedule * Client requirements and responsibilities * Completion criteria * Terms and conditions 5.3 Used a financial management system to establish the project budget and meet or exceed this established budget on a variety of complex contract types 5.4 Developed a communications management plan for using formal and consistent monthly status reports (e.g., Seven Keys ) to communicate project health and status and gained client agreement to approach 5.5 Set guidelines for estimating, planning, tracking, and forecasting an integrated project plan, managed the overall plan and delivered project as per the estimated cost and plan 5.6 Led regular project risk management reviews with project team and made significant contribution to risk or quality reviews outside own project 5.7 Established project requirements baseline that was approved by the client, gained agreement on change management process and used this process to manage multiple change requests, escalating issues as appropriate 5.8 Managed projects that meet at least five of the following criteria for 6 months: 1 - Cross border-resourcing or virtual resources 2 - Performance-based contracts 3 - Difficult project working environment that required active intervention of project manager 4 - Used multiple methodologies to direct multiple streams of work activity 5 - Managed multiple concurrent projects with teams of five or more each 6 - Managed a project which had multiple tiers of management reporting to the project manager 7 - Multiple areas within client organization directly impacted by outcomes of project 8 - More than one IBM line of business 9 - Replaced a project manager at a troubled project 10 - Managed ongoing support for critical production application or system 5.9 Established and gained client agreement on conditions of satisfaction or stakeholder agreement to project success criteria 5.10 Established issue management process to document key issues and actions requiring attention, guided team members in using these processes, and resolved issues in a timely manner 5.11 Contributed to development of others' project management skills across a project, completed Project Assessments in a timely manner, and managed a difficult human resource issue 5.12 Developed, maintained, and managed relationships at functional and executive level throughout the sponsor, project, or program organizations and provided leadership in a steering committee 5.13 Implemented plan for capturing intellectual capital on project, including inclusion in appropriate knowledge databases and reused intellectual capital at start of new projects to capitalize on lessons learned from others 5.14 Identified opportunities for follow-on business by considering multiple capabilities within IBM and worked with the account team to propose and provide strong assistance in the winning of that business ==Level 6== The capabilities below are performed as a Thought Leader. Level 6 in this dimension is obtained either by moderation from Level EDM 5 or via initial PM certification at the Executive PM level in those geos/IOTs where an EDM6 delta package is available. Please go to the PM/COE certification page for further details if you are planning to apply for Executive PM certification. 6.1 Used an approved PM methodology to manage projects that meet the following requirements: Number of projects: 4 Projects with IBM: 2 Projects completed in the last three years: 1 Duration of each project: minimum 9 months Projects with 5 or more FTEs: 2 Projects with 10 or more FTEs: 1 Projects with 20 or more FTEs: 1 Stages of the project lifecycle: all Subcontractors: multiple The total value of all projects managed total either US$20M revenue or 140,000 total hours managed during time on project(s) 6.2 Created subcontractor SOW with at least two of the following characteristics: * Fixed price * Performance-based * Defined risk sharing model * Deliverable-based pricing * Compliant with Value Creation model 6.3 Negotiated contract agreement among stakeholders, including multiple IBM functions, client executives, LoB executives, and business partners 6.4 Established a program office, or equivalent, and management processes and used structure to review status with executive level project leadership and successfully manage the program 6.5 Managed multiple tiers of project management on a single project 6.6 Identified and cultivated project management or leadership candidates through formal and informal activities and completed Project Assessments in a timely manner 6.7 Maintained long-term executive client relationships, credibility, and trust despite short-term setbacks and influenced others to do the same 6.8 Managed projects that meet two of the following criteria for 9 months: 1 - Cross-region or cross-geography implementation 2 - Multiple IBM lines of business 3 - Improved the condition of a troubled project 6.9 Contributed to IBM project management intellectual capital in one of the following ways: 1 - Developed project estimating, tracking, and forecasting tools and techniques to support project teams 2 - Provided business acumen and thought leadership in areas of program and portfolio management, contract management, financial measurement and reporting, and project governance 3 - Lead an effort to reuse assets on a client engagement [[Category:IBM]][[Category:Contract]]</text> 
