  <text xml:space="preserve">==Portfolio Areas of Concern== ===Project contract details=== ===Key contacts associated with the Project=== ===Project Approved Plan, with and without cost contingency=== ===Project Actual financials - Project to Date (PTD) and Year to Date (YTD)=== ===Outlook Financial data by month for current year, next year and 9 out years=== ===Seven Keys project health reporting for current month and rolling 12 month history=== ===COSCard repository and reporting of Overall Expectation Performance and Last/Next review dates === ===Risk Management health ratings, review details and Troubled Project details=== ==Roles and Capabilities== Role Capabilities by Role ===Project Manager (PM), Project Control Officer (PCO), Additional Editors=== 1. Ability to view and edit those Projects that they are associated with. 2. Perform the Outlook and Submission 3. Submit request for Outlook review 4. Update Seven Keys 5. Attach COSCards and update COSCard repository information 6. Submit email requesting accrual/deferral 7. Identify some roles on the Project Details tab: RFC,CSO,RM, Service Area Leader. In addition the PM & PCO can also update the PCO and Additional Editors. 8. Receive notification for pending monthly Outlook submission or PCRs 9. Receive notification of new Project creation in the BCS PMDB and reference to the Project Management Startup Checklist. ===Partner, Associate Partner, Service Area Leader === 1. Ability to view entire portfolio 2. Project Manager capabilities for those Projects that they are associated with (except to update PCO & Additional Editors on the Project Details tab). ===Regional Finance Contact (RFC)=== 1. Ability to view entire portfolio 2. Perform the Outlook, Quick Outlook and Submission 3. Submit request for Outlook review 4. Update Seven Keys 5. Attach COSCards and update COSCard repository information 6. Submit email requesting accrual/deferral 7. Perform Approved Plan override 8. Update Cost Contingency approved for use 9. Update contract terms, coverage ID, closed date, Geography,Division,RSO. 10. Mark project as closure pending if project inactive 11. Remove projects from Mandatory and cancel sending of Reminders 12. Update Outlook information for Closed projects 13. Identify some roles on the Project Details tab: RFC,CSO,RM. In addition can also update the Additional Editors. ===Contract Administrator Contact (CSO)=== 1. Ability to view entire portfolio 2. Receive accrual/deferral notifications 3. Receive email to CSO ===Accounting=== 1. Ability to view entire portfolio 2. Update Cost Contingency approved for use 3. Update the Approved Plan GP % ===Risk Manager === 1. Ability to view entire portfolio 2. Ability to update fields on Risk Management Tracked Project tab 3. Perform the Outlook and Submission 4. Submit request for Outlook review 5. Update Seven Keys 6. Attach COSCards and update COSCard repository information 7. Submit email requesting accrual/deferral 8. Enter Delivery comments: Issues, Actions, etc in Project Details tab 9. Identify some roles on the Project Details tab: RFC,CSO,RM ===Business Operations Manager (BOM)=== 1. Ability to view entire portfolio. 2. Receive notification for month end Outlook submission status for all Projects ===DBE Editors (PLMs, BOMs.)=== 1. Ability to view entire portfolio. 2. Project Manager capabilities for all Projects (except receive notifiications) 3. Edit Additional Editors & PCO field (Project Details tab) 4. Remove projects from Mandatory and cancel sending of Reminders 5. Move a project in/out of Closure Pending (no more outlook expected).. ===Service Group=== 1. Enter Delivery comments: Issues, Actions, etc in Project Details tab [[Category:Contract]][[Category:Project Management]][[Category: Portfolio Management]]</text> 
